Here you can select below various & graphic; -layouts algorithm. the entries, as they are described on the website of & graphviz; are:
& dot; -algorithm, the standard for grated graphs. the algorithm calculates the edges in the same direction (from top to bottom or from left to right) and then tries to produce short edges and as a few edge flashing.
The & neato; -algorithm is the standard for unfinished graphs. it produces representations according to the springspring model. this is used by Kamada-Kawai algorithm, which is synonymous with statistical-dimensional scaling.
The & FDP; -algorithm creates a springray model layout. it uses the Fruity-Reingold-Heuristics, and includes a plitter for the treatment of large and clustered Graphene.
The & circo; algorithm sets the nodes circular in accordance with the description of Six und Tollis, 1999, and Kauffman and Wiese, 2002. it is useful for certain diagrams of multiple cyclical structures.
